  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nNo endpoints created in the EndpointSlice for my service due to the port on the service being too long. Logs show:\r\n```\r\n1 endpointslice_controller.go:229] Error syncing endpoint slices for service \"istio-system/istio-pilot\", retrying. Error: Error updating istio-pilot-g9hz4 EndpointSlice for Service istio-system/istio-pilot: EndpointSlice.discovery.k8s.io \"istio-pilot-g9hz4\" is invalid: ports[3].name: Invalid value: \"http-legacy-discovery\": must be no more than 15 characters\r\n```\r\n\r\nEndpointSlice created has no endpoint:\r\n```\r\naddressType: IP\r\napiVersion: discovery.k8s.io/v1alpha1\r\nendpoints: null\r\nkind: EndpointSlice\r\nmetadata:\r\n  creationTimestamp: \"2019-10-25T16:39:21Z\"\r\n  generateName: istio-pilot-\r\n  generation: 1\r\n  labels:\r\n    kubernetes.io/service-name: istio-pilot\r\n  name: istio-pilot-g9hz4\r\n  namespace: istio-system\r\n  ownerReferences:\r\n  - apiVersion: v1\r\n    blockOwnerDeletion: true\r\n    controller: true\r\n    kind: Service\r\n    name: istio-pilot\r\n    uid: a2b2ea09-541e-437b-adca-e4668ad0f875\r\n  resourceVersion: \"841\"\r\n  selfLink: /apis/discovery.k8s.io/v1alpha1/namespaces/istio-system/endpointslices/istio-pilot-g9hz4\r\n  uid: a655116b-e6e8-450b-ada2-7497e47f9661\r\nports: null\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nService that works with Endpoints should work with EndpointSlice. If this is intentional, it should be clearly documented\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nCreate a service with a long port name\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.16\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: kind",
